<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" http-equiv="Content-Type" />
    <style>
      body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 1.6; color: #333; }
      .container { max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 20px; }
      .header { background-color: #ffc107; color: #212529; padding: 20px; border-radius: 5px 5px 0 0; }
      .content { background-color: #f8f9fa; padding: 20px; border: 1px solid #dee2e6; }
      .button { display: inline-block; padding: 12px 24px; background-color: #007bff; color: white; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 5px; margin-top: 15px; }
      .footer { margin-top: 20px; padding-top: 20px; border-top: 1px solid #dee2e6; font-size: 12px; color: #6c757d; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="header">
        <h1>⚠️ Missing Supplier Credentials</h1>
      </div>
      
      <div class="content">
        <p>Hello,</p>
        
        <p>Product imports for <strong><%= @supplier.name %></strong> cannot proceed because no credentials have been configured.</p>
        
        <p>As the super admin, you need to set up credentials for this supplier so that the system can import products for all users.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Next steps:</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>Log in to SupplierHub</li>
          <li>Go to Suppliers section</li>
          <li>Add your credentials for <%= @supplier.name %></li>
        </ol>
        
        <p>Once credentials are configured, imports will begin automatically on the next scheduled cycle.</p>
        
        <div class="footer">
          <p>This is an automated message from SupplierHub.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
